&lt;Alcan AluminiumwerkeGmbH>, a subsidiary of Alcan Aluminium Ltd &lt;AL.N> of Canada,said it plans to close its aluminium smelter in Ludwigshafen atthe end of June.    A spokesman said Alcan was closing the smelter, with annualcapacity of 44,000 tonnes and 320 employees, because of highelectricity costs and the low world market price of aluminium.    Alkan had said earlier this year it would close half theplant's capacity but decided to shut down completely when talkswith potential cooperation partners failed, the spokesman said.He declined to name the other companies involved in the talks. REUTER&#3;